olitics. With no role for a centralised state, the functions of coordination and administration are fulfilled through pluralist self-governance. Political intermediation proceeds via a web of functional associations, which operate within a system of revitalised communities, while management is carried out through modes of self-regulation that embody the key anarchist values of equality, solidarity and mutual-aid.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAnarchism. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aAnarchist advanced selfhood.  aDealienated labour.  aEconomic democracy.  aFreedom as autonomy.  aGuild socialism.  aLeft-libertarian political economy.  aReflective consumption.  aSelf-legislation.  aSocial anarchist organisation.  aWorker-managed cooperatives.1 aWyatt, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152617130640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526171306423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526171306/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2023